OL,3,CCarer who helped husband play football
OL,4,Cagain after brain injury up for award
OL,6,FDave had a heart attack in 2006 and
OL,7,Fsuffered an hypoxic brain injury,
OL,8,Fresulting in him losing much of his
OL,9,Fspeech and some mobility.
OL,11,FBut with Sue's help, he has been able
OL,12,Fto continue pursuing many of his
OL,13,Fhobbies and interests.
OL,15,FSue and Dave have been supported by
OL,16,Fthe brain injury charity Headway
OL,17,FTyneside for the last 10 years, and
OL,18,Fnow Jo Wallis from the charity has
OL,19,Fnominated Sue for their Carer of the
OL,20,FYear Award.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/4
